Class MazeRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • maze.Cell
      • maze.MazeRunner

  • public class MazeRunner
extends Cell
    Class used to determine if a Maze is solvable and fix the issue if it is not.

    Erick

                  int Y,
                  int W,
                  int H,
                  int cols,
                  int rows,
                  java.util.ArrayList<Cell> cells)
        Constructor for the MazeRunner
        Parameters:
        X - The 'x' position in the image.
        Y - The 'y' position in the image.
        W - The Width of the Cell.
        H - The Height of the Cell.
        cols - The No. of Columns in the Maze the runner will be in.
        rows - The No. of Rows in the Maze the runner will be in.
        cells - An ArrayList of Cells that compose the Maze that the MazeRunner will solve.

      • backtrack

        public void backtrack()
        Retrieves the last visited Cell from the Stack in order to find an untracked Cell to move onto. If the Stack becomes empty before reaching the "End" Cell of the Maze, then the Maze is unsolvable and a solvable route must be created.
